  sodium: 900 mg
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice
@yellow onion{1}(thinly sliced). Dice @tomato{1}(diced).

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon},
and a pinch of @smoked paprika{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later). Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}; set aside.

== Roasted Asparagus ==

Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%ounce}. (Save potatoes for another use.)

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon},
salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until browned and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Swap in asparagus for potatoes. Roast until tender and lightly browned, ~{10-12%minutes}.

== Tomato Onion Jam ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion
and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add tomato, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, remaining paprika, @sugar{1%teaspoon}
(2 tsp for 4 servings), and 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4). Cook, stirring, until
caramelized and jammy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to a second small bowl. Wash out pan.

== Patties ==

While onion cooks, form @ground beef{10%ounce} into two patties (four patties for
4 servings), each slightly wider than a burger bun. Season all over with salt and
pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for jam over medium-high heat. Add patties and
cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

In the last 1-2 minutes of cooking, top each patty with @gouda cheese{2%slice};
cover pan until cheese melts.

== Assembly ==

Meanwhile, halve @potato buns{2}. Toast until golden brown.

Spread bottom buns with a bit of sauce. Fill buns with patties and tomato onion
jam.

Divide burgers between plates. Serve with potato wedges on the side and remaining
sauce for dipping.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160º.